abstract: Among quarterbacks, Russell Wilson, Tony Romo and Tom Brady all move up to Tier 2 this week.
snippet: Among quarterbacks, Russell Wilson, Tony Romo and Tom Brady all move up to Tier 2 this week.
lead_paragraph: In this statistical model, I apply a clustering algorithm called the Gaussian mixture model to an aggregation of expert ranking data provided by Fantasypros.com. The algorithm finds natural tiers and clusters within the data. The charts that result visualize the tiers and help you decide your starting lineup each week.

abstract: The capital is rapidly gaining in cozy neighborhood dining spots with distinctive food.
snippet: The capital is rapidly gaining in cozy neighborhood dining spots with distinctive food.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — On a scrubby block in a working-class neighborhood east of Rock Creek Park, plopped down among cheap hair salons, a dry cleaner and a sad-looking liquor store, the future of dining in Washington, D.C., has arrived.
headline_main: Washington Has More on Its Plate
headline_print_headline: Washington Has More to Dine On

abstract: Polling in Senate races is unpredictable, largely because a Republican or Democrat in one state may differ politically from one in another state.
snippet: Polling in Senate races is unpredictable, largely because a Republican or Democrat in one state may differ politically from one in another state.
lead_paragraph: WICHITA, Kansas — Races for the United States Senate feature the same drearily familiar elements as presidential contests: partisan polarization, ideological predictability and voters with fixed opinions about well-known politicians.

abstract: The papers address Hillary Rodham Clinton’s effort to overhaul the health care system, her Senate candidacy, and the Monica Lewinsky affair.
snippet: The papers address Hillary Rodham Clinton’s effort to overhaul the health care system, her Senate candidacy, and the Monica Lewinsky affair.
lead_paragraph: The National Archives released 10,000 more pages of previously undisclosed documents from the Clinton White House on Friday, with topics including Hillary Rodham Clinton’s ill-fated attempt as first lady to overhaul the health care system.

abstract: Two Fritz Lang films new to Blu-ray are anti-Nazi statements made by this director.
snippet: Two Fritz Lang films new to Blu-ray are anti-Nazi statements made by this director.
lead_paragraph: No filmmaker more fully embodies the history of movies, at least until the mid-1960s, than Fritz Lang (1890-1976). Born in Vienna, Lang was the most commanding figure in German silent cinema. There is scarcely a popular genre — including science fiction, period spectacle, espionage, gangster and horror — that did not pass through his hands and does not bear his mark. “M” (1931), his first talkie and official masterpiece, is the original portrait of a serial killer; once in Hollywood, he created the prototype for “Bonnie and Clyde,” and pioneered film noir.

snippet: Mrs. Obama, unlike Hillary Rodham Clinton in 1998, will keep to a fairly limited path as she stumps for candidates, some of whom are trying to distance themselves from the president.
lead_paragraph: MILWAUKEE — She can rouse a crowd as she did here this week, connect with women and drive turnout among African-American voters. Yet despite the nail-biting closeness of state contests to decide which party will control the Senate, Michelle Obama has been largely absent from the campaign trail so far.

abstract: A reader asks about the commemoration of one of the worst defeats by the Continental Army, in what is now Fort Washington Park in Washington Heights.
